  "texts": [
    "Their method is tailored to physical systems in continuous time, making it inapplicable for interacting agents in the general case, since it requires explicitly enumerating allowed transitions between configurations.In contrast to these approaches, our work is the first to jointly emulate individual and stochastic interacting agents.",
    "This is particularly important, since ABMs are inherently stochastic and rely on individual-level interactions to produce emergent aggregate outcomes.",
    "Moreover, since our surrogate is differentiable by design, it paves the way for methods that estimate both individual-level parameters and state variables.To achieve this goal, our framework relies on a novel combination of graph neural networks and diffusion models.",
    "Diffusion models [14] were first introduced in the context of image generation, where they demonstrated impressive generation capabilities [7], and were then applied to other domains [18].",
    "A number of works addressed graph data [21], for example in molecule modeling [15] and protein structure generation [2]."
  ],
